kpi_info.title: period_duration (period_duration)
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: IPS_TOTAL (M563C0)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets.The total number of input IP datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADSUM (M563C1)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets with errored checksum.The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their checksums. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_TOOSMALL (M563C2)
kpi_info.use: Too small IP packets received.The number of discarded IP datagrams due to too small to contain IP packet. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_TOOSHORT (M563C3)
kpi_info.use: Too short IP packets received.The number of discarded IP datagrams with invalid data length. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_TOOLONG (M563C4)
kpi_info.use: Too long IP packets received.The number of discarded IP datagrams whose length is longer than the maximum IP packet size. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADHLEN (M563C5)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets with bad header length.The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to invalid header length. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADLEN (M563C6)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets with bad length.The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to inconsistent IP header and IP data length. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADOPTIONS (M563C7)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets with errors in IP options.The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors discovered in processing their header IP options. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADVERS (M563C8)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets with version errors.The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to version number mismatch. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_FRAGMENTS (M563C9)
kpi_info.use: IP fragments received. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_FRAGDROPPED (M563C10)
kpi_info.use: IP fragments dropped.The number of discarded IP fragments due to duplicates or out of space. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_FRAGTIMEOUT (M563C11)
kpi_info.use: IP fragments timed out.The number of IP fragments dropped after time out. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_RCVMEMDROP (M563C12)
kpi_info.use: IP fragments dropped due to lack of memory. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADFRAGS (M563C13)
kpi_info.use: Malformed IP fragments dropped. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_REASSEMBLED (M563C14)
kpi_info.use: Reassembled IP packets.The number of IP datagrams successfully re-assembled. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_DELIVERED (M563C15)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets delivered successfully.The total number of input IP datagrams successfully delivered. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_NOPROTO (M563C16)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets with unknown protocol.The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_FORWARD (M563C17)
kpi_info.use: Forwarded IP packets.The number of input IP datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route t o forward them to that final destination. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_CANTFORWARD (M563C18)
kpi_info.use: Received IP packets not forwardable.The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header destination field was not a valid address to be for warded. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_REDIRECTSENT (M563C19)
kpi_info.use: Redirect messages sent.The number of sent redirect messages. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_LOCALOUT (M563C20)
kpi_info.use: IP packets sent from this host.The total number of IP datagrams generated at the system, not forwarded. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_RAWOUT (M563C21)
kpi_info.use: Raw IP packets.The total number of IP packets generated. The number of packets sent with fabricated IP header. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_ODROPPED (M563C22)
kpi_info.use: Outgoing IP packets discarded.The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were d iscarded for resource shortages, for example lack of buffer space. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_NOROUTE (M563C23)
kpi_info.use: Outgoing IP packets, no route found.The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_FRAGMENTED (M563C24)
kpi_info.use: Outgoing IP packets fragmented.The number of outgoing IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_OFRAGMENTS (M563C25)
kpi_info.use: Outgoing IP packet fragments created.The number of outgoing IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_FASTFORWARD (M563C26)
kpi_info.use: IP packets fast-forwarded. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_CANTFRAG (M563C27)
kpi_info.use: IP packets fragment failed.The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_NOGIF (M563C28)
kpi_info.use: No match gif IP packets.Tunneling IP packets that cannot find match gif. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: IPS_BADADDR (M563C29)
kpi_info.use: Invalid address in the header of IP packet.The number of discarded IP datagrams which has failures of source address selection. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ICPS_ERROR (M563C30)

kpi_info.title: TCPS_SNDCTRL (M563C77)

kpi_info.title: TCPS_RCVBYTE (M563C84)

kpi_info.title: TCPS_RCVDUPBYTE (M563C86)

kpi_info.use: Bad data length of UDPv6 packet Number of received UPDv6 datagrams not delivered due to data length larger than packet. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_BADSUM (M563C229)
kpi_info.use: Bad checksum of UDPv6 packet Number of received UPDv6 datagrams not delivered due to checksum errors. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_NOSUM (M563C230)
kpi_info.use: Received UDPv6 packets without checksum Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_NOPORT (M563C231)
kpi_info.use: Received UDPv6 packets with no process on destination port. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_NOPORTMCAST (M563C232)
kpi_info.use: Multicast UPDv6 packets with no port The number of received UPDv6 multicast/broadcast datagrams discarded due to no process on destination port. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_FULLSOCK (M563C233)
kpi_info.use: UDPv6 packet dropped due to full socket buffers.Number of received UDPv6 datagrams not delivered because input socket buffers are full. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_PCBCACHEMISS (M563C234)
kpi_info.use: UDPv6 PCB hash misses The number of UPDv6 packets with Process Control Block (PCB) hash misses. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UDP6S_OPACKETS (M563C235)
kpi_info.use: UDPv6 packets output Total number of UDPv6 datagrams sent. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_CURRENT_ESTABLISHMENT (M563C236)
kpi_info.use: The number of associations for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED, SHUTDOWN-RECEIVED or SHUTDOWN-PENDING. When association is established.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_ACTIVE_ESTABLISHMENT (M563C237)
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the COOKIE-ECHOED state: COOKIE-ECHOED -> ESTABLISHED. The u pper layer initiated the association attempt. When association is established actively.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_PASSIVE_ESTABLISHMENT (M563C238)
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the CLOSED state: CLOSED -> ESTABLISHED. The remote endpoint initiated the association attempt. When association is established passively.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RESTARTED (M563C239)
kpi_info.use: The number of restarted SCTP associations due to peer dropped. When association is restarted.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_ABORTED (M563C240)
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from any state using the primitive 'ABORT': AnyState --Abort--> CLOSED . Ungraceful termination of the association. When association is closed with ABORT.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SHUTDOWNS (M563C241)
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SHUTDOWN-SENT state or the SHUTDOWN-ACK-SENT state. Gr aceful termination of the association. When association is closed with SHUTDOWN.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_TOO_MANY_RETRANSMISSIONS (M563C242)
kpi_info.use: The number of associations closed due to excessive. When association is closed due to excessive.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_BYTES (M563C243)
kpi_info.use: The number of bytes received in sequence. When a STCP segment s received in sequence, this counter will be updated to tell how many bytes have been received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_PACKETS (M563C244)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP packets received. Duplicatesand invalid packets are included. When a STCP packet is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_DATAGRAMS (M563C245)
kpi_info.use: The number of received valid packets. When a valid packet is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_CONTROL (M563C246)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP control chunks received (no duplicate chunks included). When a STCP segment with control chunks is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_OOTB (M563C247)
kpi_info.use: The number of out of the blue packets received by the host. An out of the blue packet is an SCTP packet correctly formed, including the proper checksum, but f or which the receiver was unable to identify an appropriate association. When a STCP segment with an out of the blue sequence is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_DUPLICATED_TSN (M563C248)
kpi_info.use: The number of received duplicated TSN. When a STCP segment with duplicate TSN is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_DROPPED_FRAGMENT (M563C249)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped invalid fragment. When invalid fragment is dropped.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_BAD_SSN (M563C250)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped chunks due to bad stream sequence number. When dropped due to bad stream sequence number.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_BAD_CSUM (M563C251)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP packets received with an invalid checksum. Dropped due to bad checksum.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_BAD_VTAG (M563C252)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped SCTP packets due to bad verification tag. Dropped due to bad verification tag.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_BAD_STREAM_NBR (M563C253)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped chunk due to bad stream number. Dropped due to bad stream number.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_IN_MULTICAST (M563C254)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped multicast SCTP packets (SCTP can't be multicast). Dropped multicast (SCTP can't be multicast).

kpi_info.title: SCTP_HEADER_DROPS (M563C255)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped SCTP packets due to bad header. Dropped due to bad header.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVE_WINDOW_DROPS (M563C256)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped SCTP packets due to no receive window. Dropped due to no receive window.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_NO_PORTS (M563C257)
kpi_info.use: The number of dropped SCTP packets due to no endpoint found for this. Dropped due to no endpoint found for this.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_NO_MEMORY (M563C258)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP chunks dropped due to no memory. Dropped due to no memory.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_BYTES (M563C259)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP bytes sent. When a STCP segment is sent, this counter will tell how many bytes have been sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_DATAGRAMS (M563C260)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP packets sent. Retransmitted DATA chunks are included. When a STCP segment whose length is more than zero is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_CONTROL (M563C261)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP control chunks sent (retransmissions are not included). Control chunks are those chunks different from DATA. When a STCP control segment is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_RETRANSMISSIONS (M563C262)
kpi_info.use: The number of retransmitted SCTP chrunks. When retransmitted STCP data is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_FAST_RETRANSMISSIONS (M563C263)
kpi_info.use: The number of fast retransmitted STCP chrunks. When fast retranmission is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_WINDOW_PROBE (M563C264)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP chrunks sent for window probes. When window probe is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_CHUNK_DATA (M563C265)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP DATA chunks received. When DATA chunk is recived.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_CHUNK_DATA (M563C266)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP DATA chunks sent. When DATA chunk is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_CHUNK_SACK (M563C267)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP SACK chunks received. When SACK chunk is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_CHUNK_SACK (M563C268)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP SACK chunks sent. When SACK chunk is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_CHUNK_HBREQ (M563C269)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP HEARTBEAT-REQ chunks received. When HEARTBEAT-REQ chunk is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_CHUNK_HBREQ (M563C270)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP HEARTBEAT-REQ chunks sent. When HEARTBEAT-REQ chunk is sent.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_RECEIVED_CHUNK_HBACK (M563C271)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP HEARTBEAT-ACK chunks received. When HEARTBEAT-ACK chunk is received.

kpi_info.title: SCTP_SENT_CHUNK_HBACK (M563C272)
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP HEARTBEAT-ACK chunks sent. When HEARTBEAT-ACK chunk is sent.
